{
  "stem": "13817.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was describing my grandmother's house were they went through like a tornado.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everything in the house was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have one picture here, which I got from my grandma when I came to the States, which is about six by three, six by four.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You can see, still, the bag of the eggs in this little picture where they even had to destroy this, which was hanging on the wall in the-- in the living room or dining room.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know which one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But even to-- down to this little picture, they had to destroy it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My grandma and my aunt climbed over fences in the back yard and through back alleys.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They made it to our house where, in fact, most of the Jewish community in that night-- at that night congregated, because, like I said, before, we were lucky.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Hardly was anything was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then, the next day, all the men between 16 and 60 were arrested and sent to various concentration camps at that time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But most of them came, after three or four months would be released.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "First, we started out with veterans from First World-- from World War I, then eventually they released more or less everybody who didn't have any police record.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They kept some who had a jaywalking record that-- longer than us or they didn't let them out at all anymore.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My brothers and I were lucky.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know whether it was lucky or not in hind-- hindsight.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because if we would have gone to the camp at that time, maybe we would have left Germany easier or earlier.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the, the chief of police of  the little town called my mother and said, let your boys go in hiding.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I have to come to arrest them.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
